"{\"abstract\":\"The increasing and flexible use of autonomous systems in many domains \\u2013 from intelligent transportation systems, information systems, to business transaction management \\u2013 has led to challenges in understanding the \\u201cnormal\\u201d and \\u201cabnormal\\u201d behaviors of those systems. As the systems may be composed of internal states and relationships among sub-systems, it requires not only warning users to anomalous situations but also provides transparency about how the anomalies deviate from normalcy for more appropriate intervention. We propose a unified anomaly discovery framework \\u201cDeepSphere\\u201d that simultaneously meet the above two requirements \\u2013 identifying the anomalous cases and further exploring the cases\\u2019 anomalous structure localized in spatial and temporal context. DeepSphere leverages deep autoencoders and hypersphere learning methods, having the capability of isolating anomaly pollution and reconstructing normal behaviors. DeepSphere does not rely on human annotated samples and can generalize to unseen data. Extensive experiments on both synthetic and real datasets demonstrate the consistent and robust performance of the proposed method.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2763546\",\"name\":\"X. Teng\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2763546\"},{\"authorId\":\"51055300\",\"name\":\"Muheng Yan\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/51055300\"},{\"authorId\":\"2532309\",\"name\":\"A. Ertugrul\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2532309\"},{\"authorId\":\"34821764\",\"name\":\"Y. Lin\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/34821764\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"32553692\",\"name\":\"Zhangyu Cheng\"},{\"authorId\":\"2705189\",\"name\":\"Chengming Zou\"},{\"authorId\":\"46436276\",\"name\":\"Jianwei Dong\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1145/3338840.3355641\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isI